*Installition of docker on ubuntu
1) $sudo apt-get update
2) $sudo apt-get install curl
3) $sudo curl -fsSL http://get.docker.com/ | sh
4) $sudo usermod -aG docker ubuntu
5) $sudo docker --version

sudo shutdown now   <-----------------------------------it is shurdown on terminl
sudo system ctl status docker <-------------------------to check the sttus
______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
*Installation of docker on amazon linux
1) sudo yum update -y
2) sudo yum install docker -y
3) sudo service docker start 
4) sudo service docker status
5) sudo docker --version
6) to exit ctrl + z
7) sudo service docker status <--------------------------------it will ckeck docker service active or not
_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
*Creat image form dockerhub
sudo docker pull imagename <-------------------------------to downlod the image form dockerhub to load mchin
sudo su  <-------------------------------------------------go to root user
sudo docker image <----------------------------------------show the images(to check all images)
sudo docker search imagename <-----------------------------to find out the images in a dockerhub
________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
*We are trying to run imges/Crreate containers
sudo docker images

sudo docker run -it --name yogesh ubuntu /bin/bash
--------------------------------------------------
run:-run at back end , 
      -it:- interactive termanal, 
      yogesh:-container name, 
      ubuntu:-imagename
--------------------------------------------------

sudo docker images <---------------------------------------it will show all the images

sudo docker ps -a  <---------------------------------------it will show all the docker containers in you machin
sudo docker ps     <---------------------------------------it will show only running continers

sudo docker start yogesh(container) <-----------------------to start the container in running state
sudo docker stop yogesh(container) <------------------------to stop the container in running state

sudo docker run -it busybox <------------------------------it will take defalt name of continer
sudo docker run -it busy box bin/bash


sudo docker rm containername <------------------------------it will remove the container
sudo docker rm containerid  <-------------------------------it will remove the container
sudo docker info <------------------------------------------show all information of docker image
                                                           -to check the information of container coun, image count,docker version, context,
sudo docker atth youges(containtername) <-------------------go inside the container
sudo docker exec -it continerid sh                         -it will redirect you inside the continer
                                                           -to ttach the continer means
sudo docker rmi busybox(imagename) <-----------------------it will remove the image 
                                                          -it will delete the doker image form machin
